\fs28 \cf10 \cb4 Given a triangle, find the minimum path sum from top to bottom. Each step you may move to adjacent numbers on the row below.\cb1 \
\cb4 For example, given the following triangle [ \cf5 2\cf10 , \cf5 3,4\cf10 , \cf5 6,5,7\cf10 , \cf5 4,1,8,3\cf10  ] The minimum path sum from top to bottom is 11 (i.e., 2 + 3 + 5 + 1 = 11).\cb1 \
\cb4 Note: Bonus point if you are able to do this using only O(n) extra space, where n is the total number of rows in the triangle.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

